UNITED STATES of America, Appellant, v. Emily Earl BOYLE, etc., Appellee. No. 8370. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. Nov. 2, 1936. Peirson M. Hall, U. S. Atty., and Ernest D. Fooks, Attorney, Department of Justice, both of Los Angeles, Cal. *1021Chenoweth & Whitehead, of Los Angeles, Cal., for appellee.

Before WILBUR, GARRECHT, and DENMAN, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Upon stipulation of counsel for respective parties, ordered appeal dismissed, that a judgment be filed and entered accordingly, and mandate issued forthwith.
